                <div class="community-forum-thread-post-body">
                    <p>Great question! For wet conditions, I typically recommend dropping your pressure by 5-10 PSI from your normal dry pressure. This increases the tire's contact patch with the road, improving grip.</p>
                    
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>I normally run 90-95 PSI on my 25mm tires in dry conditions</p>
                    </blockquote>
                    
                    <p>Given your weight and tire size, try running 80-85 PSI in wet conditions. The GP5000s have excellent wet grip, but lower pressure will help even more. Just don't go too low or you risk pinch flats.</p>
                    
                    <p>Also consider:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Reduce speed when cornering</li>
                        <li>Avoid painted lines and metal surfaces</li>
                        <li>Give yourself extra braking distance</li>
                    </ul>
