                <div class="community-forum-thread-post-body">
                    <p>I race in the Pacific Northwest where it's wet 8 months of the year. Here's my pressure formula that works great:</p>
                    
                    <pre><code>Wet PSI = (Body weight in lbs / 2) - 5</code></pre>
                    
                    <p>For your 165 lbs, that would be about 77-78 PSI. I've used this formula for years with great success. The key is finding the balance between grip and rolling resistance.</p>
                    
                    <p>Pro tip: If you're racing or doing fast group rides, maybe only drop 5 PSI. For commuting or casual rides where safety is paramount, drop the full 10-15 PSI.</p>
